article.headline: Texas A&M-Corpus Christi 81, Kent St. 73
article.story: CORPUS CHRISTI, Texas (AP) -- Chris Daniels scored 23 points to lead Texas A&M-Corpus Christi to an 81-73 win over Kent State on Tuesday night. Texas A&M-Corpus Christi (9-4) shot 60 percent from the field. Kent State (7-6) shot 49 percent from the field in the game in which the lead changed three times. Josh Washington and Josh Ervin each scored 15 points for Texas A&M-Corpus Christi. Cedric Smith scored 10 points. Omni Smith scored 30 points for Kent State. Armon Gates added 12.
